summary: Slept on time and woke up on time, reached library by 9:30 and revised DSA questions until early afternoon. After 1pm, motivation dipped and I went into autopilot mode. Cigarette intake increased and I spent more on food than I should, feeling indulgent despite financial strain. At the same time, I noticed a faint emergence of hope and self-care beneath the darker patterns. Today felt slightly better than yesterday, with a sense that tomorrow can improve further.

wins: Slept and woke on time, kept routine consistent
Showed up at library at 9:30 and did DSA revision
Noticed small signs of hope despite difficulties
losses: Spent more on food despite financial strain
ideas: Plan lighter study tasks for afternoon dip
Track cigarette count daily to keep awareness sharp
Experiment with cheaper food alternatives to control spending

goals: Do at least 1 focused DSA session in the afternoon
